  m_text: "A router connects different networks together \u2014 typically linking
    a local network (LAN) to the internet (WAN). It determines the best path for
    data to travel from one network to another. Routers also often include firewalls
    and NAT (Network Address Translation) to provide security and allow multiple
    devices to share a single public IP address."
