  m_text: A switch operates within a local network and is responsible for connecting
    multiple devices (like PCs, printers, and servers) so they can communicate efficiently.
    Unlike a hub, a switch sends data only to the intended device, improving speed
    and security. It works at Layer 2 (Data Link Layer) of the OSI model.
